 clusters and groups. We also find\nevidence for a central abundance drop in NGC 4472. The iron abundance profile\nshows that the region along the cavity system has a lower metallicity than the\nsurrounding, undisturbed gas, similar to the central region. This also shows\nthat bubbles have lifted low-metallicity gas from the center.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 11 Oct 2017 18:02:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-10-13"}
